name: TRENT 700 POWER | Air Canada A330-343 [C-GFAF] Beautiful Dusk Takeoff from Toronto Pearson! ᴴᴰ
description:
My first time flying an A330! I have to say, with the 2-4-2 seating configuration and Air Canada's older seats, this was a superb flight. Enjoy this comprehensive departure video from the busiest airport in Canada! Video log below if you want to skip to any important parts. Hope you enjoy!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

VIDEO LOG:
00:58 - Hydraulics activated.
01:20 - Flaps set to takeoff position.
02:00 - Taxi begins.
03:30 - Approaching the threshold as an Air Transat A330-200 departs before us.
05:00 - Lining up runway 24R, behind an arriving Dash 8.
05:50 - Spooling up, with that characteristic RR Trent 700 howl!
06:40 - Rotate!.
08:20 - Banking away, heading to Munich.
09:20 - Flaps up.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
